        "farm_description": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>We got our start producing field-grown plants and shipping them balled-and-burlapped (B&B). Since then, our production has shifted entirely to containerized material. Our farm consists of <strong>290 acres</strong> in southern New Jersey near the city of Bridgeton. Our growing production occurs on 2.7 million sq. feet of 'hoop houses' and 39,000 square feet of heated greenhouse space.</p>",
            "width": "100%",
            "max_width": "narrow",
